result.execSummary:
The defendant Nathan Michael Baublitz was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case. One or more other charges in this case were dismissed. The dismissed charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Nathan Michael Baublitz is presumed innocent of the dismissed charges.

  • Nathan Michael Baublitz was found guilty of Possess w/ Intent-Amphetamine(>10-50g), a class D felony, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(1m)(e)3.
  • Nathan Michael Baublitz was found guilty of Forgery-Uttering, a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 943.38(2).

records.addlTxt: Notice of Completion of Case Letter
Transcript of Sentencing Hearing Held June 23rd, 2022

1:16 PM Defendant Nathan Michael Baublitz in court, in custody.  Attorney Ellen Denise Craker in court for Nathan Michael Baublitz.  Attorney Chad C La Lor in court for State of Wisconsin. Agent Jennifer Sem with Dept of Corrections. State recommends for Count 1 - 8 years prison fashioned as 4 years initial confinement and 4 years extended supervisin and pay a $100 fine plus costs. For Count 3 - 6 years prison fashioned as 3 years initial confinement and 3 years extended supervision. Credit of 119 days. Concurrent with Count 1. State has complied with Victim's Rights. State makes argument in support of prison sentence recommendation. State reviews defendant's 21 prior convictions. Defendant was in St Louis County Drug Court while this offense occurred and on Probation for 9 felony offenses. Representative with victim, Centricity Credit Union makes a statement to the Court. Attorney Craker agrees with days credit and that defendant would be eligible for both prison programs. Attorney Craker asks for an imposed and stayed prison sentence with three years probation. Attorney Craker notes non violent past offenses. Attorney Craker notes defendant's substance abuse issues. Defendant makes statement to the Court. 

Court reviews statements and recommendations made by all parties. Court reviews factors in considering sentence. Court orders for Count 1 - 8 years prison fashioned as 4 years initial confinement and 4 years extended supervision. Pay a fine of $100 plus court costs. Conditions of extended supervision include payment of outstanding financial obligations and comply with all programming as deemed necessary by the DOC. For Count 3 - 4 years prison fashioned as 2 years initial confinement and 2 years extended supervision. Credit of 119 days. Concurrent to Count 1. Conditions of extended supervision include payment of outstanding financial obligations and comply with all programming as deemed necessary by the DOC. Defendant is eligible for substance abuse program and Challenge Incarceration program.

AND ARRAIGNMENT 02:38 PM Defendant Nathan Michael Baublitz in court with attorney Ellen Denise Craker.  Chad C La Lor appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Attorney Craker notes motion filed before Judge Thimm recused himself. Defendant has been in custody for three weeks. State is opposed to bail modification. State reviews charges and just waived extradition to St. Louis County, MN on seven cases with several failures to appear. Defendant also has several failures to appear in his criminal history all out of Minnesota. Attorney Craker notes defendant is a resident of the area and history does not include violent in nature. Court reviews factors in determining bail. Court reviews multiple failures to appear and Court denies bail modification. Attorney Craker received information, wavies reading and pleads not guilty. Court accepts not guilty plea. Changes arraignment to status conference.
Bail/bond hearing on March 18, 2022 at 02:30 pm.
